cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper focuses on comparing the performance of deep convolutional neural networks with humans in view-invariant object recognition, which is a core topic in computer vision. 
2. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses the architecture of deep neural networks and their similarity to the human visual system. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category as the paper evaluates the performance of different machine learning models in view-invariant object recognition. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the ability of deep neural networks to recognize thousands of object categories, which is a key application of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible as the paper compares the performance of deep neural networks with humans in view-invariant object recognition, which is a topic that involves both human perception and machine learning.
